  <span id="freeText8797757797166854644" style="display:none">I read the first chapter as a short story and thought it was top 5 ever. This book is the attempt to turn that short story into a novel. It didn't work well. Amongst my many troubles w the book is this sizable middle section of the protagonist leading a rebellion that turns out to be an illusion, this a waste of pages. Almost like a story that ends with the final line: but then I woke up and realized it was all just a dream". Total cop-out. This is my 2nd Swanwick novel, I doubt I will try a 3rd</span>
